The Etsu of Wako chiefdom in Kwali Area Council in the FCT, HRH Ibrahim Usman Abdulaziz, has requested the management of the newly established Viju Milk company in his chiefdom to consider employing 70 per cent indigenes of his area as junior staff of the company. HRH Abdulaziz, made the request when he and some members of his traditional council visited the companyâ€™s management located along the Abuja-Lokoja road yesterday. He said employing the youth will help reduce the rate of unemployment and also divert the attention of the youth from engaging in social vices in the area. 